+        // Invalidate prepared-statement / compiled-program / planner-directive
+        // caches whose cached plans were bound to pre-commit B-tree / WAL
+        // visibility state. Without this, a `SELECT ... WHERE pk = ?`
+        // re-issued on the same handle after a write can return zero rows
+        // (or stale/wrong rows) because the cached plan is unaware that the
+        // visible page image has changed.
+        //
+        // Guarded on `committed_write`: pure-read commits (transactions that
+        // began with BEGIN but only read) don't shift B-tree visibility, so
+        // paying the cache-clear cost there would be overhead with no
+        // correctness benefit. See issue #72.
